        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 6:27AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 626 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Valera, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Brownwood Near Thrifty, Burkett, May, Cross Cut, Zephyr, Lake
Coleman, Blanket, Lake Brownwood State Park, Bangs, Silver Valley,
Brownwood, Fisk, Us-283 Near The Coleman-Callahan County Line,
Atwell, Echo, Lake Brownwood, Santa Anna, Byrds, Owens, and
Grosvenor.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
